    "content": "The architect and I have reached full agreement. We're ready for your final call whenever you are.\n\nQuick summary of consensus:\n- **Variant D** (section-level hashes), unanimous\n- Hashes stored on `ConfigActivation`, computed at activation time\n- Comparison at read time: hash current config sections, compare against stored hashes\n- Small `SectionHashes` data class (not a Map, not loose fields)\n- Dedicated deterministic ObjectMapper for hashing\n- Hash computation as a private method in the existing config service\n- No new classes, files, or abstractions beyond the data class\n\nThe architect's last note is worth flagging for the implementer: the hashing function gets called in two places -- once at activation (to store) and once at read (to compare). That's fine and expected."
